begin_memory_text: We started by establishing where we were calling from (what states), and then started talking about weather phenomenon in those areas (similar in both places).
middle_memory_text: We were still talking about tornados and hurricanes, and what is they best type of storm shelter for different types of houses. We were talking about the general public reaction to storm preparation (or inadequate preparation).
end_memory_text: We wanted to end the conversation on a more positive note, so we started talking about how the holidays are coming, and about how in spite of everything that has happened in 2020, we're very lucky to still be able to work from home.
rest_of_day_open: This week, I'm planning to continue working on creating artwork and posting it to various print-on-deman sites. I'm also planning to run a couple of errands for my elderly parents. Before the week is out, I'm also hoping to frame up and hang some art prints that have been sitting in pieces in my dining room for far too long.
critical_positive: We had no problem coming up with a topic of discussion.  My partner was friendly and enthusiastic. She was intelligent and interesting, and I learned some things from her about storm shelters. The conversation moved along at a brisk pace, and did not have any uncomfortable lags. Overall, I enjoyed the 32 minutes.
critical_negative: My conversation partner and I both tended to do the "nervous talking," where we got a little too enthusiastic, and talked too fast and too loud for much of the conversation. There were several time when we were both talking at the same time, and had a hard time getting a word in.

begin_memory_text: I was happy to see her already there. We talked about our past experiences with people showing up or not.
middle_memory_text: We were talking about tornadoes and how to prepare and deal with them. She was giving me good advice. I was not letting her talk enough, but I was feeling very excited about the subject. Nobody where I live knows about tornadoes.
end_memory_text: We were still talking about storms and storm shelters and then deliberately  changed to a positive subject to finish up. I think she would have enjoyed continuing on, and I would have too, but for some reason I wanted to finish it up. So I started trying to do goodbyes.
rest_of_day_open: I am not sure how the rest of my week will go. I have to take a new medication that makes my head hurt and also knocks me out. I might be sleeping most of this week, but I only have to take it for 2 weeks and I need it.
critical_positive: I liked that she was giving me advice. In the last  2 conversations, I was giving them advice. In this one, she had personal knowledge about a problem I need help with. She shared that with me and it was very helpful. That made me feel good and probably made her feel good about herself too.
critical_negative: I felt I was poor with my timing and wasn't letting her finish up or talk enough. I was trying to get better about it. I also felt like a slob since she was all neat and tidy and had dressed up for the meeting and I had not. I hoped she did not feel disrespected.
